  "name": "RPlog_The_Prex_is_Dead_Long_Live_the_Prex",
  "title": "Death Throes Over Corellia",
  "summary": "As the stolen Star Destroyer Corporate Buyout breaks apart while falling toward Corellia, the bounty hunter Meissa drags his unconscious, foul-smelling Toydarian prize Qwynt through the disintegrating hangar and into a clumsy dropship for a barely controlled crash-landing. The vengeful CEC magnate Smitherbodkins, whose orbital station Qwynt's antics helped destroy, pursues in a shuttle, browbeating his pilot into docking with the plummeting dropship to stop Qwynt from reaching the ground alive. Aboard, the spice-maddened Qwynt breaks his own leg to slip his bonds, escapes into the bowels of the ship, and clambers into a folded AT-AT, idly priming its cannons. When Smitherbodkins corners him, Qwynt delivers a final, surreal revelation -- claiming to be the businessman's father, Geophreigh Smitherbodkins Qwynt III -- before Smitherbodkins runs him through with his cane-blade. Dying, Qwynt hurls a concealed axe that maims Smitherbodkins's face and leg; the cockpit erupts in flames, and the gravely wounded magnate barely drags himself from the burning wreck on the Golden Beaches, leaving Qwynt's body as a pyre and the lingering question of whether any of it was real.",
